1
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:34,320
=Hold a Court Now=

2
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:38,140
=Episode 23=

3
00:01:38,540 --> 00:01:39,490
What are you doing?

4
00:01:39,490 --> 00:01:40,570
Take a look.

5
00:01:41,490 --> 00:01:42,330
Rui,

6
00:01:42,410 --> 00:01:45,210
the whole room
is full of legal professionals.

7
00:01:45,380 --> 00:01:47,100
You can at least meet some people

8
00:01:47,100 --> 00:01:48,570
to expand your network.

9
00:01:48,570 --> 00:01:49,850
Are you dumb?

10
00:01:52,380 --> 00:01:53,690
I'm going in first.

11
00:01:54,770 --> 00:01:56,490
We can't go in together.

12
00:01:57,133 --> 00:01:59,666
With your bestie here,
who would even dare to approach you?

13
00:02:00,570 --> 00:02:01,540
Don't leave.

14
00:02:07,290 --> 00:02:09,570
We agreed to come for a free meal.

15
00:02:23,570 --> 00:02:24,380
Look.

16
00:02:25,220 --> 00:02:26,730
Our university alumni association

17
00:02:26,730 --> 00:02:28,570
is having a tea gathering tonight.

18
00:02:28,780 --> 00:02:29,690
Are you going or not?

19
00:02:29,850 --> 00:02:30,610
No.

20
00:02:35,620 --> 00:02:37,500
(Law University Alumni Reading Club)

21
00:02:39,780 --> 00:02:40,820
Take another look.

22
00:02:40,820 --> 00:02:42,130
See, there are so many people.

23
00:02:42,130 --> 00:02:43,111
It's quite interesting.

24
00:02:43,290 --> 00:02:44,100
Just go.

25
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:50,100
You can't stay cooped up
at home all the time.

26
00:02:50,500 --> 00:02:52,340
You should go out and meet new people.

27
00:02:52,610 --> 00:02:53,890
Aren't they all alumni?

28
00:02:54,170 --> 00:02:56,540
Maybe you've met them before.
How are they new?

29
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:58,410
There are always some you haven't met.

30
00:02:58,410 --> 00:03:00,540
There are always new people
beyond the ones you know.

31
00:03:00,940 --> 00:03:02,780
Why are you so stubborn?

32
00:03:03,340 --> 00:03:04,220
Are you going or not?

33
00:03:04,610 --> 00:03:05,450
No.

34
00:03:05,866 --> 00:03:07,066
If you're not going, I'm going.

35
00:03:07,540 --> 00:03:08,340
Go, please.

36
00:03:08,540 --> 00:03:15,060
(Tea Gathering)

37
00:03:15,060 --> 00:03:16,890
Excuse me, is this where we sign in?

38
00:03:18,220 --> 00:03:19,220
Yes.

39
00:03:25,340 --> 00:03:27,220
Are there any rules for this event?

40
00:03:28,380 --> 00:03:29,290
I don't think so.

41
00:03:31,130 --> 00:03:32,170
I'm here for the event too.

42
00:03:32,170 --> 00:03:33,010
I'm not sure.

43
00:03:37,450 --> 00:03:39,450
Have I seen you somewhere before?

44
00:03:57,150 --> 00:03:57,640
Hello?

45
00:03:58,260 --> 00:03:59,940
You finally picked up.

46
00:04:00,111 --> 00:04:02,450
Your dad is meeting
his old colleagues for dinner tonight.

47
00:04:02,500 --> 00:04:03,500
Are you going?

48
00:04:03,890 --> 00:04:04,850
No.

49
00:04:05,260 --> 00:04:06,940
You should at least
go out and see people.

50
00:04:06,940 --> 00:04:09,690
You can't stay cooped up
at home after work.

51
00:04:10,940 --> 00:04:12,540
I'm with Jiang Feng.

52
00:04:13,410 --> 00:04:14,410
He's at my place.

53
00:04:14,570 --> 00:04:17,700
I mean, you should have
a normal social life.

54
00:04:17,930 --> 00:04:19,340
Then go with Jiang Feng.

55
00:04:20,140 --> 00:04:22,660
They're all uncles and aunties
who watched you grow up.

56
00:04:23,290 --> 00:04:24,730
You haven't gathered in a long time.

57
00:04:25,333 --> 00:04:26,980
It'll be good to get some fresh air.

58
00:04:26,980 --> 00:04:27,930
I'm heading out now.

59
00:04:27,930 --> 00:04:29,250
I'll come pick you up right away.

60
00:04:30,250 --> 00:04:31,540
Don't come.

61
00:04:32,111 --> 00:04:34,311
Jiang Feng and I
are going to the alumni gathering.

62
00:04:34,460 --> 00:04:35,490
We're about to leave.

63
00:04:36,020 --> 00:04:37,140
Alumni gathering?

64
00:04:38,220 --> 00:04:39,290
Alright, go ahead then.

65
00:04:43,020 --> 00:04:44,540
What alumni gathering?

66
00:04:44,777 --> 00:04:46,688
Having dinner with
your parents is much better.

67
00:04:54,580 --> 00:04:55,290
Wait for me.

68
00:04:56,133 --> 00:04:57,733
(Xie Yuan)
Please don't misunderstand.

69
00:04:57,800 --> 00:04:59,170
I'm from the Legal Aid Center.

70
00:04:59,410 --> 00:05:00,460
My name is Xie Yuan.

71
00:05:02,580 --> 00:05:03,580
Xie Yuan?

72
00:05:03,980 --> 00:05:05,140
Legal aid, nice to meet you.

73
00:05:05,290 --> 00:05:06,340
I'm also a lawyer.

74
00:05:06,340 --> 00:05:08,490
I'm from Ronghe Law Firm.

75
00:05:08,490 --> 00:05:09,460
My name is Qin Rui.

76
00:05:09,540 --> 00:05:10,460
Qin Rui?

77
00:05:11,220 --> 00:05:12,660
You're Qin Rui?

78
00:05:12,900 --> 00:05:14,810
No wonder you looked so familiar.

79
00:05:16,020 --> 00:05:17,930
I've been following your video account,

80
00:05:18,220 --> 00:05:19,460
Rui's Legal Lens, right?

81
00:05:19,540 --> 00:05:20,440
Thank you.

82
00:05:20,440 --> 00:05:23,100
I've followed you for a long time.
I didn't expect to run into you here today.

83
00:05:23,580 --> 00:05:24,980
I think many of your viewpoints

84
00:05:25,140 --> 00:05:26,610
are excellent.

85
00:05:26,850 --> 00:05:29,220
I often leave
comments under your videos.

86
00:05:29,220 --> 00:05:30,410
You even replied to me before.

87
00:05:30,850 --> 00:05:31,660
What a coincidence.

88
00:05:33,888 --> 00:05:35,050
I've seen some of the comments

89
00:05:35,050 --> 00:05:37,050
under your videos too.

90
00:05:37,155 --> 00:05:38,920
I don't think you need
to take them to heart.

91
00:05:38,955 --> 00:05:39,822
The internet

92
00:05:39,866 --> 00:05:41,250
is just a place for people to vent.

93
00:05:41,370 --> 00:05:42,933
Behind a screen, you don't even know

94
00:05:43,022 --> 00:05:44,700
who you're talking to.

95
00:05:45,100 --> 00:05:46,100
And some people

96
00:05:46,170 --> 00:05:47,290
haven't even understood

97
00:05:47,290 --> 00:05:48,700
the full story,

98
00:05:48,700 --> 00:05:50,900
yet they make one-sided
judgments and comments.

99
00:05:51,066 --> 00:05:53,140
Netizens only stay interested
for a short while.

100
00:05:53,540 --> 00:05:55,410
When you achieve something
even better someday,

101
00:05:55,810 --> 00:05:57,460
they'll come back and praise you again.

102
00:05:58,850 --> 00:06:00,170
Thank you for telling me all this.

103
00:06:00,377 --> 00:06:02,490
Looks like you really have
been following me.

104
00:06:03,580 --> 00:06:05,050
Hurry up.

105
00:06:09,170 --> 00:06:09,780
Hello.

106
00:06:09,780 --> 00:06:10,250
Excuse me,

107
00:06:10,250 --> 00:06:11,980
where is the tea gathering?

108
00:06:12,088 --> 00:06:13,930
The matchmaking event, right?
Downstairs.

109
00:06:13,930 --> 00:06:15,020
Got it. Thanks.

110
00:06:17,170 --> 00:06:18,460
Matchmaking event?

111
00:06:19,780 --> 00:06:21,980
Just treat it as a tea gathering.

112
00:06:22,370 --> 00:06:23,900
Grab a bottle of water and sit there.

113
00:06:23,900 --> 00:06:25,930
It's fine. You'll eventually
forget Qin Rui anyway.

114
00:06:25,930 --> 00:06:27,780
The two of you are just
parallel lines now.

115
00:06:27,790 --> 00:06:28,730
If you cross paths again,

116
00:06:28,730 --> 00:06:30,050
I'll write my last name backwards.

117
00:06:39,700 --> 00:06:40,700
See?

118
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:41,900
Isn't that nice?

119
00:06:44,540 --> 00:06:45,540
Shen.

120
00:06:50,930 --> 00:06:51,810
Lan?

121
00:06:51,900 --> 00:06:54,020
Shen, I didn't expect
you to be here too.

122
00:06:57,140 --> 00:06:57,810
Signing in here.

123
00:06:57,810 --> 00:06:58,810
Help me sign in.

124
00:07:02,410 --> 00:07:03,930
Lan, long time no see.

125
00:07:04,410 --> 00:07:05,340
Long time no see.

126
00:07:23,730 --> 00:07:24,850
Let's go.

127
00:07:35,290 --> 00:07:36,340
Long time no see.

128
00:07:37,370 --> 00:07:38,370
Long time no see.

129
00:07:40,290 --> 00:07:41,370
How have you been?

130
00:07:41,730 --> 00:07:43,020
Have you been well

131
00:07:44,140 --> 00:07:45,170
at Ronghe Law Firm lately?

132
00:07:45,930 --> 00:07:46,850
Pretty good.

133
00:07:50,100 --> 00:07:51,610
Judge Shen, you must be doing well too,

134
00:07:51,730 --> 00:07:53,266
even coming to a matchmaking event.

135
00:07:53,290 --> 00:07:54,610
I just saw an empty table over there.

136
00:07:54,610 --> 00:07:55,850
Why don't you go chat there?

137
00:07:56,020 --> 00:07:58,050
Come on, this way.

138
00:07:58,340 --> 00:07:59,700
You guys enjoy yourselves.

139
00:08:03,460 --> 00:08:04,580
See?

140
00:08:04,850 --> 00:08:06,410
She's already moved on

141
00:08:06,410 --> 00:08:08,460
and is ready to start a new life.

142
00:08:08,660 --> 00:08:10,490
You shouldn't keep hanging on either.

143
00:08:11,177 --> 00:08:13,460
I almost thought I'd have to
write my last name backwards.

144
00:08:19,580 --> 00:08:21,580
Sit here, sit.

145
00:08:22,580 --> 00:08:23,220
Then you...

146
00:08:23,220 --> 00:08:25,370
You two take your time,
I won't interrupt.

147
00:08:27,290 --> 00:08:29,100
Seniors, you can sit
anywhere that's free.

148
00:08:29,100 --> 00:08:30,100
Let's sit here.

149
00:08:30,580 --> 00:08:31,490
Let's go.

150
00:08:31,730 --> 00:08:33,340
I'll get you something to drink.

151
00:08:37,940 --> 00:08:39,340
I really didn't know she'd be here.

152
00:09:04,220 --> 00:09:05,220
Sorry.

153
00:09:10,250 --> 00:09:11,250
Who's that?

154
00:09:15,610 --> 00:09:17,530
He seems to be

155
00:09:17,650 --> 00:09:19,610
from the Chenxi Legal Aid Center.

156
00:09:20,370 --> 00:09:21,340
His name is...

157
00:09:22,980 --> 00:09:23,980
Xie Yuan?

158
00:09:25,180 --> 00:09:26,250
Right, Xie Yuan.

159
00:09:27,610 --> 00:09:28,770
Let me explain first.

160
00:09:29,022 --> 00:09:31,130
Actually, I didn't come here
for matchmaking today.

161
00:09:32,650 --> 00:09:34,530
Not afraid you'll laugh at me,

162
00:09:36,010 --> 00:09:37,820
I originally came just for a free meal.

163
00:09:38,850 --> 00:09:40,610
Didn't expect it to turn out like this.

164
00:09:41,820 --> 00:09:42,980
Actually, today,

165
00:09:43,130 --> 00:09:44,610
I'm not here for matchmaking either.

166
00:09:44,770 --> 00:09:45,940
I came hoping to find

167
00:09:45,940 --> 00:09:46,940
lawyers willing

168
00:09:46,940 --> 00:09:48,460
to take on legal aid cases.

169
00:09:48,940 --> 00:09:50,250
A large portion of our cases

170
00:09:50,250 --> 00:09:51,850
are from the Family Court.

171
00:09:52,340 --> 00:09:54,730
We want to help those

172
00:09:54,770 --> 00:09:56,666
who are treated unfairly
within their families,

173
00:09:56,940 --> 00:09:58,100
to give them support.

174
00:10:00,370 --> 00:10:01,370
Alright, enough.

175
00:10:01,820 --> 00:10:03,890
She's already moved on emotionally.

176
00:10:03,890 --> 00:10:04,940
You still can't let go?

177
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:09,820
I know this might be a bit abrupt,

178
00:10:09,820 --> 00:10:12,130
but I'm not sure if you'd be interested.

179
00:10:14,180 --> 00:10:16,370
I used to handle Family Court cases too,

180
00:10:16,610 --> 00:10:18,850
so I've heard about this area,

181
00:10:19,420 --> 00:10:20,650
but I don't know it very well.

182
00:10:21,220 --> 00:10:22,460
Let me explain it to you.

183
00:10:24,700 --> 00:10:25,610
Look.

184
00:10:26,610 --> 00:10:27,820
Take a look at these photos.

185
00:10:31,420 --> 00:10:32,340
Do you know,

186
00:10:32,888 --> 00:10:33,822
recently, Qin Rui

187
00:10:33,830 --> 00:10:35,460
acted as defense counsel
for Ren Haiping,

188
00:10:35,460 --> 00:10:37,133
and she's been
heavily criticized for it.

189
00:10:37,250 --> 00:10:38,940
She's only been
at Ronghe for a few days,

190
00:10:38,940 --> 00:10:40,311
but how did she turn into this?

191
00:10:41,130 --> 00:10:42,220
Turn into what?

192
00:10:42,460 --> 00:10:43,370
Look.

193
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:45,250
Qin Rui used to care about money,

194
00:10:45,250 --> 00:10:46,533
but she earned it the right way.

195
00:10:46,610 --> 00:10:48,770
So why is she helping Ren Haiping now?

196
00:10:49,700 --> 00:10:51,530
You're a judge.

197
00:10:52,180 --> 00:10:54,610
Don't make assumptions
if you don't know the truth.

198
00:10:56,340 --> 00:10:57,890
Why are you taking it out on me?

199
00:11:01,220 --> 00:11:02,650
This just means you haven't let go.

200
00:11:03,177 --> 00:11:05,770
If you haven't let go, go to
say something while you still can,

201
00:11:05,770 --> 00:11:07,100
so you won't regret it again.

202
00:11:07,580 --> 00:11:08,940
Who says I haven't let go?

203
00:11:10,220 --> 00:11:12,100
Fine. Then stay here
and think it through,

204
00:11:12,100 --> 00:11:13,488
whether you've really let go or not.

205
00:11:13,533 --> 00:11:14,600
I'm going to get a drink.

206
00:11:20,420 --> 00:11:22,130
Most of us think

207
00:11:22,180 --> 00:11:24,060
that only women suffer
from domestic violence.

208
00:11:24,060 --> 00:11:24,820
But

209
00:11:24,820 --> 00:11:26,580
there are also some men

210
00:11:26,820 --> 00:11:28,130
who suffer from it.

211
00:11:31,610 --> 00:11:32,940
However,

212
00:11:33,220 --> 00:11:34,300
because of pride,

213
00:11:34,300 --> 00:11:36,250
they don't seek help.

214
00:11:39,770 --> 00:11:41,650
And in some cases,

215
00:11:41,850 --> 00:11:43,890
they simply have nowhere to turn.

216
00:11:44,580 --> 00:11:45,730
So in the end,

217
00:11:45,730 --> 00:11:47,820
they may take extreme actions.

218
00:11:47,980 --> 00:11:49,730
That's not what we want to see.

219
00:11:54,060 --> 00:11:55,530
So what we hope is

220
00:11:55,850 --> 00:11:58,060
to have more people join us

221
00:11:59,010 --> 00:12:00,530
and to spread awareness more widely

222
00:12:00,530 --> 00:12:02,100
so people know our organization exists.

223
00:12:03,220 --> 00:12:04,420
At critical moments,

224
00:12:04,420 --> 00:12:05,580
they can trust us

225
00:12:05,890 --> 00:12:06,890
and seek help from us.

226
00:12:07,650 --> 00:12:09,250
Look, these.

227
00:12:18,460 --> 00:12:19,370
Xiezhi,

228
00:12:19,610 --> 00:12:20,530
have some water.

229
00:12:21,460 --> 00:12:22,490
Thank you, Lan.

230
00:12:22,610 --> 00:12:24,460
Try this cake. We made it ourselves.

231
00:12:24,530 --> 00:12:25,340
Alright.

232
00:12:25,650 --> 00:12:26,650
Thank you.

233
00:12:27,820 --> 00:12:28,940
How is it, Xiezhi?

234
00:12:28,940 --> 00:12:30,340
How has work been lately?

235
00:12:32,940 --> 00:12:33,820
Quite smooth.

236
00:12:33,820 --> 00:12:35,400
What about you? Where are you working?

237
00:12:35,650 --> 00:12:37,370
I haven't found a job yet.

238
00:12:37,460 --> 00:12:38,420
I'm not in a hurry.

239
00:12:38,650 --> 00:12:39,940
I organized this event first.

240
00:12:41,530 --> 00:12:42,650
You organized it?

241
00:12:43,610 --> 00:12:44,610
That's great.

242
00:12:44,850 --> 00:12:45,850
Indeed.

243
00:12:45,940 --> 00:12:47,530
As for legal aid,

244
00:12:47,530 --> 00:12:49,340
it may be different
from your usual work,

245
00:12:49,580 --> 00:12:52,770
and you may need to find a balance.

246
00:12:55,850 --> 00:12:56,940
But we truly hope

247
00:12:56,940 --> 00:12:58,340
more people can join us

248
00:12:58,340 --> 00:12:59,420
and give us their support.

249
00:13:00,340 --> 00:13:01,300
We really need people,

250
00:13:01,300 --> 00:13:02,730
especially someone like you,

251
00:13:03,820 --> 00:13:05,300
who has the ability to help us.

252
00:13:05,770 --> 00:13:07,370
Your video account

253
00:13:07,370 --> 00:13:08,820
also has a lot of influence.

254
00:13:09,730 --> 00:13:11,700
I didn't expect
that after meeting you today,

255
00:13:12,444 --> 00:13:13,220
I'd be this happy.

256
00:13:13,220 --> 00:13:14,730
I came today to find

257
00:13:14,730 --> 00:13:16,250
like-minded people

258
00:13:16,250 --> 00:13:17,466
to work with us on legal aid.

259
00:13:17,577 --> 00:13:19,460
And it isn't easy.

260
00:13:19,770 --> 00:13:21,610
I'm glad today to have learned so much

261
00:13:21,610 --> 00:13:23,130
about legal aid.

262
00:13:24,460 --> 00:13:25,370
So,

263
00:13:25,940 --> 00:13:28,890
would you be interested in joining
the Legal Aid Center?

264
00:13:30,220 --> 00:13:31,060
It would be nice

265
00:13:31,060 --> 00:13:32,940
if I get the chance
to visit in the future.

266
00:13:32,940 --> 00:13:34,770
Why don't we add each other on WeChat?

267
00:13:35,650 --> 00:13:36,890
That would be great.

268
00:13:37,850 --> 00:13:38,820
Scan mine?

269
00:13:43,460 --> 00:13:45,250
When are you usually free?

270
00:13:46,940 --> 00:13:49,180
Weekends are generally
more convenient for us.

271
00:13:50,490 --> 00:13:51,060
Alright.

272
00:13:51,060 --> 00:13:53,100
If I have time and want to go,

273
00:13:53,100 --> 00:13:54,300
I'll contact you.

274
00:13:54,370 --> 00:13:55,530
I'm going to find my friend.

275
00:13:56,266 --> 00:13:57,100
- Okay, thanks.
- Okay.

276
00:13:57,100 --> 00:13:58,370
We'll meet again if there's a chance.

277
00:13:58,370 --> 00:13:58,650
Sure.

278
00:13:58,650 --> 00:13:59,580
Thank you.

279
00:14:06,580 --> 00:14:08,220
Do you still remember
the case last time?

280
00:14:08,370 --> 00:14:09,580
You even came to me for advice.

281
00:14:09,580 --> 00:14:11,060
Yes, thank you, Feng.

282
00:14:11,060 --> 00:14:12,250
No problem.

283
00:14:12,250 --> 00:14:14,010
Shen, has work been going well lately?

284
00:14:14,010 --> 00:14:14,700
Yes, quite well.

285
00:14:14,700 --> 00:14:16,580
Just a lot of cases recently.

286
00:14:16,650 --> 00:14:18,444
Have you met anyone
you're interested in?

287
00:14:20,340 --> 00:14:22,580
- Long time no see.
- Long time no see.

288
00:14:22,770 --> 00:14:23,940
Is that your friend?

289
00:14:24,530 --> 00:14:26,300
She doesn't seem to be in a good mood.

290
00:14:37,850 --> 00:14:39,010
Still working in forensics?

291
00:14:40,340 --> 00:14:41,250
Yes.

292
00:14:41,511 --> 00:14:42,730
You have to take a look, right?

293
00:14:42,730 --> 00:14:44,300
There are so many people here.

294
00:14:44,300 --> 00:14:45,730
- Yeah, take a look.
- Right.

295
00:14:57,300 --> 00:14:58,300
Congratulations.

296
00:14:58,955 --> 00:15:01,890
Congratulations, Shen, on your
upcoming position at the High Court.

297
00:15:02,940 --> 00:15:03,940
Work hard too.

298
00:15:04,060 --> 00:15:04,940
Wait for me,

299
00:15:05,060 --> 00:15:07,022
I'll go to the High Court
and be your assistant.

300
00:15:07,820 --> 00:15:08,700
Deal.

301
00:15:08,700 --> 00:15:09,250
Alright.

302
00:15:09,890 --> 00:15:11,610
You be Jiang's assistant,

303
00:15:11,610 --> 00:15:13,220
and I'll be Shen's assistant.

304
00:15:25,770 --> 00:15:27,060
Not in a good mood?

305
00:15:31,770 --> 00:15:33,420
Because of Shen Xiezhi, right?

306
00:15:35,460 --> 00:15:37,730
Didn't expect him to come here
for matchmaking too.

307
00:15:39,220 --> 00:15:40,940
Didn't you also add someone on WeChat?

308
00:15:41,060 --> 00:15:42,130
You're not losing.

309
00:15:42,340 --> 00:15:44,650
He's from the Legal Aid Center.

310
00:15:45,890 --> 00:15:47,010
He just came to ask

311
00:15:47,130 --> 00:15:48,370
if I wanted to join them.

312
00:15:51,100 --> 00:15:53,490
I knew it. No wonder he told you
three times tonight

313
00:15:53,490 --> 00:15:55,340
to contact him.

314
00:15:57,610 --> 00:15:59,250
You came here for matchmaking yourself.

315
00:15:59,250 --> 00:16:01,130
I don't know how it went for you,

316
00:16:01,420 --> 00:16:03,180
but you heard everything at my table.

317
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:04,650
You heard it pretty clearly.

318
00:16:05,820 --> 00:16:06,940
Caught by you.

319
00:16:08,420 --> 00:16:09,940
With a whole room full of people,

320
00:16:10,060 --> 00:16:12,370
the one I care about most is still you.

321
00:16:14,730 --> 00:16:15,820
But tonight,

322
00:16:16,650 --> 00:16:18,300
the moment I said I'm a forensic doctor,

323
00:16:18,940 --> 00:16:19,940
everyone ran away.

324
00:16:19,940 --> 00:16:22,220
Too timid. They won't achieve much.

325
00:16:22,220 --> 00:16:23,340
I rejected them.

326
00:16:24,980 --> 00:16:27,610
You barely even saw
Shen Xiezhi all night.

327
00:16:28,180 --> 00:16:29,770
Did you reject him too?

328
00:16:32,220 --> 00:16:33,940
You should worry more about yourself.

329
00:16:35,610 --> 00:16:37,250
I'd like to,

330
00:16:39,130 --> 00:16:41,300
but I've got no luck in love.

331
00:16:41,977 --> 00:16:43,577
No luck in love, but the car's here.

332
00:16:43,770 --> 00:16:44,610
Are we going or not?

333
00:16:44,820 --> 00:16:45,700
Let's go.

334
00:16:48,490 --> 00:16:49,490
Slow down.

335
00:16:52,610 --> 00:16:53,650
Slow down.

336
00:16:56,130 --> 00:16:58,010
- Slow down.
- Slow down.

337
00:16:58,010 --> 00:16:59,180
Careful, careful.

338
00:16:59,340 --> 00:17:00,130
Alright.

339
00:17:01,100 --> 00:17:01,980
Bye.

340
00:17:03,300 --> 00:17:04,180
What are you doing?

341
00:17:04,266 --> 00:17:05,533
What's that supposed to mean?

342
00:17:09,422 --> 00:17:10,460
Shouldn't you be a gentleman

343
00:17:10,460 --> 00:17:12,140
and walk her to the entrance?

344
00:17:14,460 --> 00:17:15,700
What kind of person are you?

345
00:17:16,420 --> 00:17:18,140
What kind of person are you?

346
00:17:18,266 --> 00:17:19,622
You just got your heart broken,

347
00:17:19,711 --> 00:17:21,488
and you can't stand seeing me
get a second chance.

348
00:17:21,577 --> 00:17:22,380
You're jealous?

349
00:17:22,530 --> 00:17:23,490
Oh, Jiang Feng,

350
00:17:23,490 --> 00:17:25,180
now I see you clearly.

351
00:17:25,555 --> 00:17:27,420
Go on and start your
second chance already.

352
00:17:30,290 --> 00:17:31,010
Lan.

353
00:17:31,010 --> 00:17:32,330
Lan, take care on the way.

354
00:17:32,530 --> 00:17:33,090
Bye.

355
00:17:33,250 --> 00:17:34,700
- Bye.
- Bye.

356
00:17:44,220 --> 00:17:45,250
Has it arrived?

357
00:17:45,900 --> 00:17:46,860
Over there.

358
00:18:00,488 --> 00:18:01,940
Nothing else needs to be said.

359
00:18:02,140 --> 00:18:03,460
I don't accept mediation!

360
00:18:03,940 --> 00:18:04,940
Yuanbao's dad,

361
00:18:05,810 --> 00:18:06,940
I'm sorry.

362
00:18:07,050 --> 00:18:08,290
I'll kneel to you.

363
00:18:09,460 --> 00:18:09,810
Ma'am.

364
00:18:09,810 --> 00:18:10,900
You can't leave.

365
00:18:10,940 --> 00:18:11,940
Let's get up first.

366
00:18:12,460 --> 00:18:13,380
Yuanbao's dad,

367
00:18:14,220 --> 00:18:15,490
I've wronged you.

368
00:18:16,140 --> 00:18:18,140
You can hit me or scold me,

369
00:18:18,770 --> 00:18:19,900
but you can't leave.

370
00:18:20,420 --> 00:18:21,460
Yuanbao's dad...

371
00:18:21,940 --> 00:18:23,010
I'm not his father.

372
00:18:23,010 --> 00:18:24,530
I don't have that kind of blessing.

373
00:18:24,810 --> 00:18:25,730
Let go of me.

374
00:18:26,090 --> 00:18:26,810
Let go...

375
00:18:26,810 --> 00:18:28,460
Yuanbao's dad,

376
00:18:29,180 --> 00:18:30,980
the child is closest to you.

377
00:18:30,980 --> 00:18:32,700
If he comes home and can't find you,

378
00:18:32,700 --> 00:18:34,730
he'll be frantic. Yuanbao's dad,

379
00:18:34,730 --> 00:18:36,090
I'm begging you.

380
00:18:36,090 --> 00:18:37,010
Let go!

381
00:18:37,010 --> 00:18:38,866
- I'm begging you.
- Sir, please calm down.

382
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:40,730
Don't get physical. Let's talk this out.

383
00:18:40,730 --> 00:18:41,190
Please...

384
00:18:41,266 --> 00:18:42,770
Ma'am, let's get up and talk, come on.

385
00:18:44,940 --> 00:18:46,530
I don't accept mediation.

386
00:18:46,810 --> 00:18:48,530
I'm filing for divorce.

387
00:18:48,530 --> 00:18:50,070
I want a divorce!

388
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:55,839
(DNA marker analysis
shows Wang Changxing)

389
00:18:55,840 --> 00:18:56,955
(is not the biological father
of Wang Yuanbao.)

390
00:18:59,100 --> 00:19:00,909
(The results do not
support Wang Changxing)

391
00:19:00,910 --> 00:19:02,311
(as the biological father
of Wang Yuanbao.)

392
00:19:10,940 --> 00:19:12,250
This is the last tough case.

393
00:19:16,940 --> 00:19:18,940
No idea if we can get through it.

394
00:19:19,140 --> 00:19:20,860
Don't worry, it'll be fine.

395
00:19:25,220 --> 00:19:27,700
If the divorce is granted,
won't this family fall apart?

396
00:19:27,860 --> 00:19:29,590
The plaintiff is elderly
and in poor health,

397
00:19:29,644 --> 00:19:30,530
covered in illnesses,

398
00:19:31,050 --> 00:19:33,250
and relies entirely
on the defendant for daily care.

399
00:19:33,380 --> 00:19:34,530
The defendant has no income

400
00:19:34,900 --> 00:19:36,530
and depends on the plaintiff to get by.

401
00:19:36,530 --> 00:19:38,569
There's a little over two thousand
a month in pension,

402
00:19:38,570 --> 00:19:41,244
plus a little over one thousand
in disability benefits for the son.

403
00:19:41,460 --> 00:19:42,860
There are usually no major expenses,

404
00:19:42,900 --> 00:19:44,730
so they can barely make ends meet.

405
00:19:44,770 --> 00:19:46,844
But if the divorce is granted,
who gets the house?

406
00:19:46,933 --> 00:19:47,620
Who moves out?

407
00:19:49,177 --> 00:19:51,380
The old man only has a little
over two thousand a month.

408
00:19:51,490 --> 00:19:52,220
After paying rent,

409
00:19:52,250 --> 00:19:54,250
there won't be enough left to live on.

410
00:19:54,380 --> 00:19:55,700
And as for the old lady,

411
00:19:55,700 --> 00:19:57,544
she only has a little
over one thousand a month,

412
00:19:57,544 --> 00:19:59,644
and she has to take her disabled
son with her if she moves out.

413
00:20:01,220 --> 00:20:02,530
This family of three

414
00:20:03,290 --> 00:20:05,660
at least supports each other
when they're together

415
00:20:05,660 --> 00:20:06,700
and can barely get by.

416
00:20:06,980 --> 00:20:08,140
But if they divorce,

417
00:20:08,700 --> 00:20:09,730
what will they do?

418
00:20:11,866 --> 00:20:13,050
The problem is,

419
00:20:13,688 --> 00:20:16,222
after raising this intellectually
disabled son for so many years,

420
00:20:16,288 --> 00:20:18,444
he turns out not to be
his biological child.

421
00:20:19,050 --> 00:20:21,330
No one could swallow that.

422
00:20:23,010 --> 00:20:24,180
How can this be resolved?

423
00:20:27,740 --> 00:20:29,460
Good morning, Judge Shen.

424
00:20:29,460 --> 00:20:30,290
Morning.

425
00:20:34,900 --> 00:20:36,050
♪All the little things♪

426
00:20:36,050 --> 00:20:38,460
♪Between you and me♪

427
00:20:38,460 --> 00:20:41,010
♪Woven into our lives♪

428
00:20:41,900 --> 00:20:43,660
♪The building blocks of life♪

429
00:20:43,660 --> 00:20:44,980
(Forensic Identification Center)
Please take a look at this report.

430
00:20:44,980 --> 00:20:46,333
If everything's fine, sign here.

431
00:20:46,460 --> 00:20:47,010
Hello.

432
00:20:47,010 --> 00:20:48,050
Judge Shen, you're here.

433
00:20:48,140 --> 00:20:50,355
Director Li is waiting for you.
You can go straight to him.

434
00:20:50,377 --> 00:20:51,220
Alright, thank you.

435
00:20:51,560 --> 00:20:53,480
♪Some questions♪

436
00:20:53,480 --> 00:20:55,430
♪Weigh like mountains♪

437
00:20:55,850 --> 00:21:00,440
♪How do we piece life back together?♪

438
00:21:01,240 --> 00:21:04,740
♪So hate can fade
and love feels new again♪

439
00:21:04,780 --> 00:21:05,977
(Total: 719,900.8 yuan)

440
00:21:06,066 --> 00:21:08,500
♪Reclaim the barren parts of life♪

441
00:21:08,900 --> 00:21:09,860
(To-Do Today: 1. Study and analyze last
year's non-litigation cases at the firm)

442
00:21:13,740 --> 00:21:16,140
(International accident
insurance claim case)

443
00:21:17,860 --> 00:21:18,980
Here, this is for you.

444
00:21:20,180 --> 00:21:21,977
What time did you
get off work last night?

445
00:21:22,420 --> 00:21:23,620
10:30 PM.

446
00:21:23,770 --> 00:21:24,770
Why so early?

447
00:21:24,844 --> 00:21:26,050
Director, yesterday, I...

448
00:21:26,050 --> 00:21:27,290
I don't want to hear excuses!

449
00:21:27,810 --> 00:21:29,730
All I know is,
you still haven't provided me

450
00:21:29,900 --> 00:21:30,911
with the legal analysis

451
00:21:30,977 --> 00:21:31,810
on the termination

452
00:21:31,810 --> 00:21:33,290
of Jintang Group's IPO.

453
00:21:33,290 --> 00:21:34,400
And you haven't turned in

454
00:21:34,488 --> 00:21:36,355
the due diligence report
for Huilong Group either.

455
00:21:36,620 --> 00:21:37,900
Do you remember

456
00:21:37,900 --> 00:21:39,420
your billable hours last year?

457
00:21:40,050 --> 00:21:42,050
I had 1,900 hours last year.

458
00:21:42,050 --> 00:21:43,420
Do you know how many I had?

459
00:21:43,730 --> 00:21:45,090
I'm someone close to retirement,

460
00:21:45,090 --> 00:21:46,620
and I still logged 2,500 hours.

461
00:21:46,860 --> 00:21:49,140
Young people,
you're not working hard enough.

462
00:21:49,780 --> 00:21:52,500
♪Where fairness stands♪

463
00:21:52,530 --> 00:21:53,330
Come on in.

464
00:21:55,090 --> 00:21:56,050
Mr. Li.

465
00:21:57,250 --> 00:21:58,330
Judge Shen.

466
00:21:59,530 --> 00:22:01,111
I was just telling Zhang this morning

467
00:22:01,177 --> 00:22:02,530
to send the report over to you

468
00:22:02,530 --> 00:22:04,460
so that you wouldn't come in person.

469
00:22:04,460 --> 00:22:06,250
You're quite meticulous.

470
00:22:06,570 --> 00:22:07,250
It's nothing.

471
00:22:07,250 --> 00:22:08,890
The main thing is,
the parties are anxious.

472
00:22:08,900 --> 00:22:10,311
They've been under a lot of stress.

473
00:22:10,420 --> 00:22:11,570
Getting the result earlier

474
00:22:11,620 --> 00:22:12,933
will give them some peace of mind.

475
00:22:13,330 --> 00:22:14,180
I see.

476
00:22:14,460 --> 00:22:15,420
But

477
00:22:18,530 --> 00:22:19,660
this result...

478
00:22:23,822 --> 00:22:26,222
It doesn't support
a father-son relationship, right?

479
00:22:28,900 --> 00:22:30,980
Actually, this test
wasn't really necessary.

480
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:32,240
Fangyuan is also

481
00:22:32,240 --> 00:22:34,380
(Forensic Opinion Report)
a well-known institution in the field.

482
00:22:34,380 --> 00:22:36,700
Its authority is no less than ours.

483
00:22:36,860 --> 00:22:37,900
I understand.

484
00:22:38,860 --> 00:22:40,911
Without this result,
it would be difficult

485
00:22:40,977 --> 00:22:43,420
to even begin a conversation
with the parties.

486
00:22:44,330 --> 00:22:45,140
Thank you, Mr. Li.

487
00:22:45,140 --> 00:22:46,250
No problem.

488
00:22:50,480 --> 00:22:51,090
Hello?

489
00:22:51,090 --> 00:22:52,980
Hello, Qingcheng Family Court,
this is Yu Le.

490
00:22:53,420 --> 00:22:55,900
Hello, Judge Yu, this is Shi Xiaomei.

491
00:22:57,460 --> 00:22:58,220
Hello.

492
00:22:58,290 --> 00:22:59,290
It's like this,

493
00:22:59,660 --> 00:23:02,420
I just called Judge Shu's office,

494
00:23:02,420 --> 00:23:03,460
but no one picked up,

495
00:23:03,530 --> 00:23:05,420
so I'm calling you instead.

496
00:23:05,660 --> 00:23:07,140
I hope I'm not disturbing you.

497
00:23:07,244 --> 00:23:08,620
You're not disturbing me at all.

498
00:23:08,770 --> 00:23:10,570
Ms. Shu happens to be
in a meeting right now.

499
00:23:10,570 --> 00:23:12,090
If you have anything, you can tell me.

500
00:23:12,220 --> 00:23:14,530
I just wanted to ask,

501
00:23:14,730 --> 00:23:16,420
if I find a job,

502
00:23:16,511 --> 00:23:17,866
will the chances of getting custody

503
00:23:18,050 --> 00:23:19,570
of all three children

504
00:23:20,090 --> 00:23:21,460
be much higher?

505
00:23:22,770 --> 00:23:23,620
Sorry,

506
00:23:23,620 --> 00:23:25,980
we can't disclose that.

507
00:23:26,530 --> 00:23:27,490
But

508
00:23:27,900 --> 00:23:28,660
it could be

509
00:23:28,660 --> 00:23:30,420
one of the factors we consider.

510
00:23:30,770 --> 00:23:32,330
Of course I hope

511
00:23:32,420 --> 00:23:33,770
my children can live better lives.

512
00:23:34,090 --> 00:23:35,700
They won't have to suffer with me.

513
00:23:36,380 --> 00:23:36,980
So right now,

514
00:23:36,980 --> 00:23:38,730
I've already started looking for a job.

515
00:23:38,860 --> 00:23:40,620
Oh, right, I just finished an interview.

516
00:23:40,860 --> 00:23:42,460
They had a good impression of me.

517
00:23:42,980 --> 00:23:45,380
I might get a result
in the next few days.

518
00:23:47,090 --> 00:23:49,010
That's great.
Congratulations in advance.

519
00:23:50,220 --> 00:23:51,570
But then again,

520
00:23:51,810 --> 00:23:53,380
you're taking care of three children

521
00:23:53,380 --> 00:23:54,570
while job hunting.

522
00:23:54,770 --> 00:23:56,290
That's really tough.

523
00:23:56,420 --> 00:23:57,380
Judge Yu,

524
00:23:58,860 --> 00:23:59,900
actually,

525
00:24:01,220 --> 00:24:03,090
I've only now truly understood

526
00:24:03,466 --> 00:24:05,180
what it means to say
a mother becomes strong

527
00:24:05,180 --> 00:24:07,570
for her children.

528
00:24:07,810 --> 00:24:09,900
Before this, even though I was a mother,

529
00:24:10,380 --> 00:24:13,010
I relied on my mother-in-law
for everything.

530
00:24:13,420 --> 00:24:14,810
I treated marriage

531
00:24:15,090 --> 00:24:16,860
as a safe haven where I could slack off.

532
00:24:16,980 --> 00:24:18,050
And that's how

533
00:24:18,380 --> 00:24:20,180
my life ended up like this.

534
00:24:23,620 --> 00:24:24,700
But it's alright.

535
00:24:24,770 --> 00:24:26,090
Now I understand

536
00:24:26,140 --> 00:24:27,250
what I should do

537
00:24:27,980 --> 00:24:29,620
and how I should live.

538
00:24:30,860 --> 00:24:31,660
I see.

539
00:24:32,330 --> 00:24:34,090
How are the children?

540
00:24:34,090 --> 00:24:35,090
Are they doing okay?

541
00:24:35,180 --> 00:24:36,490
They're all doing well.

542
00:24:36,620 --> 00:24:38,250
Du has really grown up.

543
00:24:38,250 --> 00:24:39,420
When I'm busy,

544
00:24:39,420 --> 00:24:41,380
she can help take care
of her younger siblings.

545
00:24:41,660 --> 00:24:43,460
And my mom also comes by often.

546
00:24:43,490 --> 00:24:44,490
That's good.

547
00:24:44,530 --> 00:24:45,220
In that case,

548
00:24:45,220 --> 00:24:47,010
if there's anything you need from us,

549
00:24:47,220 --> 00:24:48,180
just let me know.

550
00:24:48,460 --> 00:24:50,010
Thank you, Judge Yu.

551
00:24:51,570 --> 00:24:53,180
I have another interview later,

552
00:24:53,620 --> 00:24:55,900
so I won't take up more of your time.

553
00:24:56,290 --> 00:24:57,660
Alright. Wishing you success.

554
00:24:58,620 --> 00:24:59,860
Okay, goodbye.

555
00:25:10,380 --> 00:25:11,330
Come on in.

556
00:25:12,140 --> 00:25:13,770
Ms. Lou, you wanted to see me?

557
00:25:14,050 --> 00:25:15,140
Come on in.

558
00:25:19,250 --> 00:25:20,010
Have a seat.

559
00:25:23,490 --> 00:25:25,180
How is the Hehua Insurance case going?

560
00:25:25,180 --> 00:25:26,130
Have you made any progress?

561
00:25:26,140 --> 00:25:27,180
I'm organizing the materials.

562
00:25:27,180 --> 00:25:28,600
I can submit an initial proposal to you

563
00:25:28,622 --> 00:25:29,660
before the end of the day.

564
00:25:29,810 --> 00:25:30,770
No rush.

565
00:25:31,066 --> 00:25:32,810
Those two parties
are both quite stubborn.

566
00:25:32,933 --> 00:25:34,770
They won't accept
an ordinary proposal anyway.

567
00:25:34,940 --> 00:25:36,180
You don't need to rush it

568
00:25:36,220 --> 00:25:37,530
and force something out for me.

569
00:25:40,330 --> 00:25:41,810
If you run into any bottlenecks,

570
00:25:41,955 --> 00:25:43,140
don't push through on your own.

571
00:25:43,220 --> 00:25:44,290
Just tell me,

572
00:25:44,466 --> 00:25:45,660
and I'll help you resolve it.

573
00:25:46,700 --> 00:25:47,770
Thank you, Ms. Lou.

574
00:25:48,140 --> 00:25:49,530
It's alright. I just

575
00:25:50,010 --> 00:25:51,380
need a bit more time.

576
00:25:51,490 --> 00:25:53,090
I can handle it myself.

577
00:25:56,288 --> 00:25:57,730
There are many kinds of employees.

578
00:25:58,220 --> 00:26:00,700
You're someone who can
take responsibility, handle pressure,

579
00:26:00,700 --> 00:26:01,644
and doesn't complain.

580
00:26:01,860 --> 00:26:03,570
Of course I should reciprocate.

581
00:26:05,420 --> 00:26:06,730
In the future, I hope

582
00:26:06,730 --> 00:26:08,530
you'll be capable and able to

583
00:26:09,330 --> 00:26:10,570
handle cases independently.

584
00:26:11,490 --> 00:26:13,050
But for now, there's no rush.

585
00:26:13,180 --> 00:26:14,220
Slow down,

586
00:26:14,290 --> 00:26:15,660
follow your own pace.

587
00:26:16,620 --> 00:26:17,940
Take this time

588
00:26:17,940 --> 00:26:19,490
to do what you want to do.

589
00:26:19,810 --> 00:26:21,730
Don't wait
until you're overwhelmed later.

590
00:26:21,730 --> 00:26:23,900
I won't just leave you
on your own either.

591
00:26:24,620 --> 00:26:25,570
Thank you, Ms. Lou.

592
00:26:25,620 --> 00:26:27,700
Actually, I've noticed that our firm

593
00:26:27,730 --> 00:26:29,770
hasn't met
this year's legal aid hours yet.

594
00:26:29,770 --> 00:26:30,810
I also looked into it,

595
00:26:30,810 --> 00:26:34,050
and there's a legal aid center
called Chenxi.

596
00:26:34,530 --> 00:26:36,180
If I have time this weekend,

597
00:26:36,180 --> 00:26:37,333
I'd like to go check it out.

598
00:26:37,420 --> 00:26:39,180
Legal aid. That's good.

599
00:26:39,980 --> 00:26:40,900
Go ahead.

600
00:27:06,770 --> 00:27:08,770
Here, Judge, have some water.

601
00:27:09,140 --> 00:27:10,730
Thank you, Madam Qiu.

602
00:27:12,866 --> 00:27:14,660
Where are the old gentleman and Yuanbao?

603
00:27:14,730 --> 00:27:16,050
They went out for a walk.

604
00:27:16,090 --> 00:27:17,250
Yuanbao

605
00:27:17,466 --> 00:27:19,600
gets restless if he doesn't go out
at the usual time,

606
00:27:20,090 --> 00:27:21,330
crying and shouting,

607
00:27:21,810 --> 00:27:23,050
making things uneasy.

608
00:27:27,050 --> 00:27:28,290
The test results

609
00:27:28,530 --> 00:27:30,330
from your side are out, right?

610
00:27:50,100 --> 00:27:55,340
(The results do not support Wang Changxing
as the biological father of Wang Yuanbao)

611
00:28:08,730 --> 00:28:10,570
I've brought this upon myself.

612
00:28:13,010 --> 00:28:13,980
I deserve it.

613
00:28:14,620 --> 00:28:15,620
Ma'am,

614
00:28:16,730 --> 00:28:17,980
from what we understand,

615
00:28:18,088 --> 00:28:19,755
your relationship with your husband

616
00:28:19,800 --> 00:28:20,933
has always been very good.

617
00:28:21,290 --> 00:28:23,050
What exactly happened in between?

618
00:28:23,330 --> 00:28:24,810
Could you tell us?

619
00:28:29,940 --> 00:28:31,180
Back then, he and I

620
00:28:32,460 --> 00:28:34,770
were already preparing to get married.

621
00:28:36,380 --> 00:28:37,620
But his family

622
00:28:37,620 --> 00:28:39,330
was very dissatisfied with me.

623
00:28:39,770 --> 00:28:42,010
While he was working in the mine,

624
00:28:42,666 --> 00:28:44,380
they called off
the engagement on his behalf.

625
00:28:44,860 --> 00:28:45,860
After that,

626
00:28:45,900 --> 00:28:48,090
I couldn't stay in my hometown anymore.

627
00:28:48,180 --> 00:28:49,250
I had no choice

628
00:28:50,700 --> 00:28:51,900
but to follow my aunt

629
00:28:52,460 --> 00:28:53,860
and go work out of town.

630
00:28:54,620 --> 00:28:56,330
Once, during a dinner with coworkers,

631
00:28:57,770 --> 00:28:59,330
I tried to drown my sorrows in alcohol.

632
00:29:00,050 --> 00:29:01,530
I had a few drinks

633
00:29:02,250 --> 00:29:03,420
and lost my senses.

634
00:29:05,220 --> 00:29:06,700
I was taken advantage of.

635
00:29:09,770 --> 00:29:11,330
I had no way to speak up.

636
00:29:13,330 --> 00:29:15,490
More than a month later,
he came to find me.

637
00:29:17,090 --> 00:29:19,490
I didn't know how to tell him.

638
00:29:20,090 --> 00:29:21,090
I...

639
00:29:29,810 --> 00:29:30,730
Here, Madam Qiu.

640
00:29:30,730 --> 00:29:31,660
Thank you.

641
00:29:35,290 --> 00:29:37,620
Not long after, we still got married.

642
00:29:38,490 --> 00:29:40,140
After Yuanbao was born,

643
00:29:40,860 --> 00:29:42,810
we thought he was just premature.

644
00:29:44,220 --> 00:29:45,980
I truly didn't expect this.

645
00:29:49,490 --> 00:29:51,050
It's all my fault.

646
00:29:53,420 --> 00:29:55,140
I've ruined him.

647
00:29:58,940 --> 00:29:59,860
Ma'am,

648
00:29:59,980 --> 00:30:01,660
please don't blame yourself too much.

649
00:30:01,700 --> 00:30:03,250
No one wanted this to happen.

650
00:30:03,466 --> 00:30:05,140
Where are the old gentleman and Yuanbao?

651
00:30:05,460 --> 00:30:06,660
I think this matter

652
00:30:06,660 --> 00:30:09,290
should still be discussed
face-to-face with him.

653
00:30:24,050 --> 00:30:24,900
Sir,

654
00:30:26,010 --> 00:30:27,810
your wife has already told us

655
00:30:27,810 --> 00:30:29,333
everything that happened back then.

656
00:30:29,400 --> 00:30:30,700
What's done is done.

657
00:30:31,050 --> 00:30:32,290
She didn't

658
00:30:32,290 --> 00:30:33,490
intend to deceive you.

659
00:30:33,660 --> 00:30:35,050
So today,

660
00:30:35,940 --> 00:30:37,490
can we calmly

661
00:30:37,660 --> 00:30:39,250
talk this through?

662
00:30:39,460 --> 00:30:40,530
Back then?

663
00:30:40,860 --> 00:30:42,330
Back then, why didn't she say it?

664
00:30:43,140 --> 00:30:44,530
If I hadn't had that fall,

665
00:30:44,860 --> 00:30:47,290
I wouldn't even know
my own blood type to this day.

666
00:30:47,860 --> 00:30:49,050
All my life,

667
00:30:49,290 --> 00:30:51,660
I've been raising someone else's son.

668
00:30:52,490 --> 00:30:53,490
Dad.

669
00:30:56,380 --> 00:30:57,250
I'm fine.

670
00:30:57,250 --> 00:30:58,140
Go play.

671
00:30:58,220 --> 00:30:59,860
It's fine, go play.

672
00:31:07,730 --> 00:31:09,140
Yuanbao was born premature

673
00:31:09,620 --> 00:31:11,140
and developed this condition.

674
00:31:11,810 --> 00:31:13,140
When he's stable,

675
00:31:13,530 --> 00:31:14,770
he just seems a bit slow.

676
00:31:14,770 --> 00:31:16,090
But when he has an episode,

677
00:31:16,090 --> 00:31:18,010
he completely loses control.

678
00:31:19,220 --> 00:31:20,490
I used to think,

679
00:31:20,555 --> 00:31:22,777
he's my son,
so I have to take responsibility.

680
00:31:24,250 --> 00:31:25,420
As long as I raised him,

681
00:31:26,380 --> 00:31:27,730
he could still call me Dad.

682
00:31:28,180 --> 00:31:29,420
When I fell,

683
00:31:30,050 --> 00:31:31,380
he knew how to call for help

684
00:31:32,010 --> 00:31:33,010
and saved my life.

685
00:31:33,980 --> 00:31:35,140
He even knew to cry

686
00:31:35,460 --> 00:31:36,700
and care about me.

687
00:31:37,980 --> 00:31:39,620
I had nothing to complain about.

688
00:31:41,570 --> 00:31:42,490
But

689
00:31:44,220 --> 00:31:45,290
now,

690
00:31:47,490 --> 00:31:48,660
turns out...

691
00:31:52,730 --> 00:31:55,290
I've been raising someone else's son.

692
00:31:55,620 --> 00:31:59,180
What debt did I owe in my past life?

693
00:32:05,460 --> 00:32:06,380
Sir,

694
00:32:06,460 --> 00:32:07,570
please don't get agitated.

695
00:32:08,490 --> 00:32:10,180
After these rounds of mediation,

696
00:32:10,570 --> 00:32:11,730
in our view,

697
00:32:11,940 --> 00:32:13,180
your bond with Yuanbao

698
00:32:13,180 --> 00:32:15,380
is even closer
than most fathers and sons.

699
00:32:15,730 --> 00:32:16,730
Yuanbao

700
00:32:17,140 --> 00:32:19,250
trusts you and depends on you.

701
00:32:19,420 --> 00:32:21,570
Yes, you see,
he's been protecting you too,

702
00:32:21,770 --> 00:32:23,660
as if he's afraid we might mistreat you.

703
00:32:23,860 --> 00:32:25,140
What's the point of that?

704
00:32:28,900 --> 00:32:30,090
At this stage,

705
00:32:31,380 --> 00:32:32,980
I have nothing left to complain about.

706
00:32:34,900 --> 00:32:36,180
They can have everything.

707
00:32:36,420 --> 00:32:37,490
I don't want anything.

708
00:32:39,530 --> 00:32:40,530
But sir,

709
00:32:41,860 --> 00:32:43,730
if you divorce your wife,

710
00:32:44,570 --> 00:32:46,620
given your current condition,

711
00:32:47,220 --> 00:32:48,940
how will you manage alone

712
00:32:49,810 --> 00:32:51,980
without her care?

713
00:32:52,600 --> 00:32:54,620
That's not something
you need to worry about.

714
00:32:56,250 --> 00:32:57,290
Like I said,

715
00:32:57,700 --> 00:32:58,660
I refuse mediation.

716
00:32:59,570 --> 00:33:00,530
As for the child,

717
00:33:00,900 --> 00:33:02,420
whoever wants him can take him.

718
00:33:02,980 --> 00:33:03,900
As for me,

719
00:33:04,290 --> 00:33:05,380
I don't want him anymore.

720
00:33:07,660 --> 00:33:08,530
Dad,

721
00:33:09,940 --> 00:33:10,810
you don't want

722
00:33:11,380 --> 00:33:12,330
me.

723
00:33:17,530 --> 00:33:18,420
Dad.

724
00:33:19,050 --> 00:33:20,700
Don't follow me!

725
00:33:20,770 --> 00:33:21,940
Don't follow me.

726
00:33:38,980 --> 00:33:40,530
Dad.

727
00:33:45,180 --> 00:33:46,140
Dad.

728
00:34:05,380 --> 00:34:06,730
The mistake was mine.

729
00:34:06,980 --> 00:34:08,300
I've ruined his whole life.

730
00:34:08,650 --> 00:34:09,780
I agree to the divorce.

731
00:34:10,980 --> 00:34:12,210
I've thought it through.

732
00:34:12,530 --> 00:34:13,690
I'll take my son with me.

733
00:34:13,690 --> 00:34:15,090
I don't want anything else.

734
00:34:18,844 --> 00:34:20,780
We wouldn't be able
to make use of it anyway.

735
00:34:21,570 --> 00:34:23,090
Let it count as making amends to him.

736
00:34:32,610 --> 00:34:34,820
In principle, based on the fault,

737
00:34:35,010 --> 00:34:37,260
the house should indeed
be awarded to Mr. Wang.

738
00:34:37,420 --> 00:34:39,466
But the old lady
still has to care for her son.

739
00:34:39,610 --> 00:34:41,860
Relying on less than two thousand
a month in assistance

740
00:34:42,090 --> 00:34:43,170
and paying rent,

741
00:34:43,210 --> 00:34:45,170
life would truly be unsustainable.

742
00:34:46,900 --> 00:34:49,130
You've already started planning
the property division?

743
00:34:49,420 --> 00:34:50,490
Haven't you?

744
00:34:52,050 --> 00:34:52,980
Do you think

745
00:34:52,980 --> 00:34:55,088
there's still room
to turn things around with him?

746
00:34:55,622 --> 00:34:57,900
The old couple still
has deep feelings for each other.

747
00:34:57,940 --> 00:34:59,900
After all, they've been through
so much together.

748
00:35:00,300 --> 00:35:02,690
Forty years of ups and downs.

749
00:35:03,010 --> 00:35:04,570
How many families can say that?

750
00:35:05,610 --> 00:35:07,010
I can actually tell

751
00:35:07,130 --> 00:35:08,530
that even though he speaks harshly,

752
00:35:08,860 --> 00:35:10,780
he still has feelings for his son.

753
00:35:11,210 --> 00:35:12,820
After all, forty years of habit

754
00:35:13,210 --> 00:35:14,844
won't disappear overnight.

755
00:35:14,950 --> 00:35:16,888
But that doesn't mean
he still has the strength

756
00:35:16,911 --> 00:35:18,530
to treat them the way he used to.

757
00:35:18,650 --> 00:35:20,380
Besides, even if
reconciliation is possible,

758
00:35:20,690 --> 00:35:22,690
it won't happen overnight.

759
00:35:22,980 --> 00:35:24,570
Still, we have to try.

760
00:35:25,111 --> 00:35:26,900
I can't end up
tearing apart a fragile family

761
00:35:26,900 --> 00:35:28,170
just for the sake of

762
00:35:28,420 --> 00:35:30,860
meeting my own deadline, right?

763
00:35:31,420 --> 00:35:32,570
So, what do you plan to do?

764
00:35:33,300 --> 00:35:34,300
Process a handover

765
00:35:34,610 --> 00:35:36,190
and let Chief Judge Shu
handle it slowly?

766
00:35:39,050 --> 00:35:40,260
I don't know

767
00:35:40,260 --> 00:35:41,780
if the old lady can hold on that long.

768
00:35:43,900 --> 00:35:44,980
I'm not sure

769
00:35:45,340 --> 00:35:46,490
if I'm right,

770
00:35:46,490 --> 00:35:48,090
but I have a feeling

771
00:35:48,380 --> 00:35:49,420
that

772
00:35:49,420 --> 00:35:51,980
the old lady might take her son...

773
00:35:52,210 --> 00:35:53,490
Try to end their lives.

774
00:35:54,340 --> 00:35:55,380
You think so too?

775
00:35:56,690 --> 00:35:58,490
I thought I was just overthinking.

776
00:36:04,380 --> 00:36:06,780
Any plans tonight?

777
00:36:06,780 --> 00:36:08,090
How about we grab dinner

778
00:36:08,420 --> 00:36:09,460
and talk it through?

779
00:36:09,460 --> 00:36:11,380
I've made plans with someone.

780
00:36:13,530 --> 00:36:14,650
Alright, no problem.

781
00:36:14,980 --> 00:36:16,300
I'll think it through myself.

782
00:36:23,490 --> 00:36:25,490
It's fine. Enjoy your meal.

783
00:36:26,980 --> 00:36:28,490
I've started to not dislike

784
00:36:28,980 --> 00:36:30,740
the smell of food
as much since yesterday.

785
00:36:30,740 --> 00:36:31,690
Look,

786
00:36:31,900 --> 00:36:33,570
I've already eaten half a box.

787
00:36:34,690 --> 00:36:35,610
You scared me.

788
00:36:35,610 --> 00:36:36,130
I thought

789
00:36:36,130 --> 00:36:37,820
even eating alone in my office

790
00:36:37,820 --> 00:36:39,260
was enough to drive you out.

791
00:36:40,355 --> 00:36:42,377
You're not even having morning sickness.

792
00:36:42,490 --> 00:36:43,820
Why the frown?

793
00:36:45,340 --> 00:36:47,780
It's still about Shi Xiaomei's case.

794
00:36:47,900 --> 00:36:50,690
Honestly, I really don't know
how to rule on it.

795
00:36:51,900 --> 00:36:53,490
Do you think it's possible

796
00:36:53,570 --> 00:36:55,490
to grant her custody
of all three children?

797
00:36:55,740 --> 00:36:58,010
Duan Ziping's request
is quite reasonable.

798
00:36:58,340 --> 00:36:59,911
Given Shi Xiaomei's financial situation,

799
00:36:59,933 --> 00:37:02,330
she really doesn't have the ability
to support three children.

800
00:37:02,377 --> 00:37:04,210
But don't you think,
compared to Duan Ziping,

801
00:37:04,210 --> 00:37:06,340
Shi Xiaomei is more suited
to be the parent?

802
00:37:06,900 --> 00:37:07,570
For the sake

803
00:37:07,570 --> 00:37:10,010
of her children's healthy growth,

804
00:37:10,090 --> 00:37:12,300
Shi Xiaomei has chosen
to push herself forward

805
00:37:12,380 --> 00:37:14,650
to strive and better herself.

806
00:37:14,780 --> 00:37:15,820
That's quite admirable.

807
00:37:15,980 --> 00:37:17,010
Honestly,

808
00:37:17,010 --> 00:37:18,650
if I were in her position,

809
00:37:19,010 --> 00:37:21,300
I'm not sure I'd have
that kind of determination.

810
00:37:21,980 --> 00:37:23,210
Calm down.

811
00:37:23,340 --> 00:37:25,380
Your hormones are all over
the place right now.

812
00:37:25,822 --> 00:37:28,050
She even gave false testimony
in court the other day.

813
00:37:28,050 --> 00:37:28,980
Did you forget?

814
00:37:29,460 --> 00:37:30,940
If she hadn't stopped in time,

815
00:37:30,940 --> 00:37:32,610
she would've been detained.

816
00:37:33,010 --> 00:37:35,130
Besides, she doesn't even have
an income right now.

817
00:37:35,340 --> 00:37:37,170
How is she supposed
to raise three children?

818
00:37:37,420 --> 00:37:38,860
You've never raised a child.

819
00:37:39,380 --> 00:37:41,380
It takes a lot of time and energy.

820
00:37:41,490 --> 00:37:43,460
Just raising Fei alone

821
00:37:43,650 --> 00:37:45,980
has already taken so much
of my effort and time.

822
00:37:46,300 --> 00:37:48,380
Shi Xiaomei may have the will
but not the means.

823
00:37:48,530 --> 00:37:49,690
That's the core issue.

824
00:37:50,010 --> 00:37:51,900
But she's already looking for a job.

825
00:37:52,780 --> 00:37:53,820
In that case,

826
00:37:54,050 --> 00:37:55,170
even if they divorce,

827
00:37:55,170 --> 00:37:56,530
no matter who gets custody,

828
00:37:56,622 --> 00:37:58,050
the blood ties with the grandparents

829
00:37:58,050 --> 00:37:59,010
won't change,

830
00:37:59,010 --> 00:38:00,050
right?

831
00:38:00,780 --> 00:38:03,130
And besides, people can grow.

832
00:38:03,210 --> 00:38:05,010
With Shi Xiaomei's current drive,

833
00:38:05,010 --> 00:38:06,860
maybe she can balance
both family and career

834
00:38:07,260 --> 00:38:09,740
in the future?

835
00:38:11,420 --> 00:38:13,460
Perhaps pursuing a career
and raising children

836
00:38:13,490 --> 00:38:15,130
can help find common ground.

837
00:38:15,820 --> 00:38:17,420
Hope it helps unlock her potential.

838
00:38:17,570 --> 00:38:19,800
It's just hard to know
what difficulties she'll face.

839
00:38:20,340 --> 00:38:22,130
Even if Duan Ziping
isn't the most reliable,

840
00:38:22,210 --> 00:38:23,900
he has a house, a car, and savings.

841
00:38:24,010 --> 00:38:25,340
And there's also the grandmother,

842
00:38:25,420 --> 00:38:26,820
who can help out.

843
00:38:28,210 --> 00:38:29,420
I think

844
00:38:29,490 --> 00:38:31,740
a stable life, with no worries
about food or clothing,

845
00:38:31,860 --> 00:38:33,420
and having family around,

846
00:38:33,420 --> 00:38:35,530
is the best option for the children.

847
00:38:36,900 --> 00:38:38,530
Actually, I also know

848
00:38:38,577 --> 00:38:40,777
that granting custody
of all three children

849
00:38:40,844 --> 00:38:42,533
to the mother isn't realistic.

850
00:38:42,777 --> 00:38:44,380
Besides, you can tell the grandmother

851
00:38:44,380 --> 00:38:46,210
cares about the three children.

852
00:38:46,820 --> 00:38:48,820
You know, these kids

853
00:38:48,980 --> 00:38:50,644
have grown up together since childhood,

854
00:38:50,690 --> 00:38:53,010
their bond is so strong,
and their relationship so close.

855
00:38:53,010 --> 00:38:54,800
Just because their parents
are getting divorced,

856
00:38:54,844 --> 00:38:55,820
they're being forced apart.

857
00:38:55,820 --> 00:38:57,210
It hurts me.

858
00:39:01,980 --> 00:39:03,340
It really does.

859
00:39:12,710 --> 00:39:15,580
♪Turn around for every part of life♪

860
00:39:16,090 --> 00:39:19,750
♪Rushing between buildings♪

861
00:39:21,690 --> 00:39:24,330
♪Caught in the grind of daily living♪

862
00:39:24,570 --> 00:39:28,320
♪Facing the surging waves of life♪

863
00:39:29,860 --> 00:39:33,260
♪Hearing the ticking
of a wound-up spring♪

864
00:39:34,500 --> 00:39:35,220
(Jiang Feng)

865
00:39:38,860 --> 00:39:42,120
♪For the distant place we long to reach♪

866
00:39:44,820 --> 00:39:46,980
(Shen Xiezhi: Are you off work?)

867
00:39:47,940 --> 00:39:49,170
I'm on my way.

868
00:39:51,460 --> 00:39:54,460
♪Unfolding a story
full of twists with courage♪

869
00:39:54,460 --> 00:39:56,500
(Are you on your way to see me?)

870
00:39:56,500 --> 00:40:00,240
♪Through wind and across rivers♪

871
00:40:00,260 --> 00:40:02,980
Not to see you.
I'm on my way to meet Lan.

872
00:40:03,490 --> 00:40:05,490
Her friend gave her two tickets

873
00:40:05,490 --> 00:40:08,090
so we could visit an exhibition
at the modern art museum.

874
00:40:08,420 --> 00:40:10,090
After that, we might grab a meal,

875
00:40:10,090 --> 00:40:11,490
or maybe not.

876
00:40:12,010 --> 00:40:13,820
What, do you want me to come over now?

877
00:40:14,490 --> 00:40:16,170
I can tell her to cancel.

878
00:40:18,400 --> 00:40:23,720
♪Like a migrating flock♪

879
00:40:23,720 --> 00:40:27,700
(No need. I'm afraid if you come now.
I don't want to entertain you.)

880
00:40:31,620 --> 00:40:33,180
(Shen Xiezhi)

881
00:40:35,820 --> 00:40:38,020
(Jiang Feng)

882
00:40:41,210 --> 00:40:42,010
What?

883
00:40:42,740 --> 00:40:45,090
If you want me to come, just say it.

884
00:40:45,090 --> 00:40:45,490
Right?

885
00:40:45,490 --> 00:40:47,010
I'm really free right now.

886
00:40:47,222 --> 00:40:49,933
No need. I've arranged to meet
an agent to look at apartments.

887
00:40:50,740 --> 00:40:51,740
Looking at apartments?

888
00:40:51,900 --> 00:40:53,010
Alright then, go ahead.

889
00:40:53,490 --> 00:40:54,690
If I finish early,

890
00:40:54,690 --> 00:40:56,260
I'll find you for a late-night meal.

891
00:40:56,420 --> 00:40:57,340
Okay.

892
00:40:57,420 --> 00:40:58,300
Bye.

893
00:41:07,100 --> 00:41:17,940
(Chenxi Legal Aid Center)

894
00:41:21,940 --> 00:41:23,170
Hello, who are you looking for?

895
00:41:23,340 --> 00:41:25,340
Excuse me, is Xie Yuan here?

896
00:41:25,460 --> 00:41:27,000
He's in the office on the third floor.

897
00:41:27,170 --> 00:41:27,780
Thank you.

898
00:41:27,780 --> 00:41:28,650
You're welcome.

899
00:41:29,300 --> 00:41:31,050
Alright, I'll be there soon.

900
00:41:36,820 --> 00:41:38,050
- Are you okay?
- I'm fine.

901
00:41:38,460 --> 00:41:39,340
Mo.

902
00:41:40,900 --> 00:41:42,130
Are you okay, kid?

903
00:41:44,380 --> 00:41:46,050
We made a promise with you.

904
00:41:46,460 --> 00:41:47,690
We'll protect you.

905
00:41:48,490 --> 00:41:50,260
Come with me, let's cut the cake.

906
00:41:50,490 --> 00:41:51,490
It's your favorite,

907
00:41:51,900 --> 00:41:52,860
and it's sweet.

908
00:41:55,210 --> 00:41:56,050
Come on.

909
00:41:56,610 --> 00:41:57,490
Go ahead.

910
00:41:59,820 --> 00:42:01,130
I'll take him over first.

911
00:42:01,690 --> 00:42:02,420
Let's go.

912
00:42:03,300 --> 00:42:04,610
Are you alright? Let me see.

913
00:42:07,460 --> 00:42:09,170
Sorry, I bumped into you just now.

914
00:42:10,300 --> 00:42:11,090
Are you okay?

915
00:42:11,090 --> 00:42:13,050
I'm fine, just a small bump.

916
00:42:13,980 --> 00:42:24,260
(Tianhai City High People's Court)

917
00:42:39,010 --> 00:42:40,900
(From aspiring to become a judge,)

918
00:42:41,000 --> 00:42:42,955
(to entering
the Intermediate People's Court,)

919
00:42:43,010 --> 00:42:44,820
(then being transferred
to Qingcheng Court,)

920
00:42:45,260 --> 00:42:47,130
(and becoming a Family Court judge,)

921
00:42:47,610 --> 00:42:49,530
(now I'm finally able
to realize my ambition.)

922
00:42:51,420 --> 00:42:53,090
(A judge may be lonely,)

923
00:42:53,610 --> 00:42:55,380
(they must restrain their emotions)

924
00:42:55,530 --> 00:42:58,130
(to uphold justice and remain fearless.)

925
00:42:59,090 --> 00:43:00,610
(This profession)

926
00:43:00,610 --> 00:43:02,090
(has never been an easy choice,)

927
00:43:02,333 --> 00:43:03,688
(nor one to hesitate over.)

928
00:43:14,620 --> 00:43:18,080
♪All the little things
between you and me♪

929
00:43:18,080 --> 00:43:20,760
♪Woven into our lives♪

930
00:43:21,610 --> 00:43:23,590
♪The building blocks of life♪

931
00:43:23,590 --> 00:43:25,290
♪Shape the sky above us♪

932
00:43:25,290 --> 00:43:27,450
♪Are you doing alright?♪

933
00:43:27,770 --> 00:43:30,450
♪What are you struggling for?♪

934
00:43:31,330 --> 00:43:35,150
♪Some questions weigh like mountains♪

935
00:43:35,530 --> 00:43:40,380
♪How do we piece life back together?♪

936
00:43:40,940 --> 00:43:45,130
♪So hate can fade
and love feels new again♪

937
00:43:45,130 --> 00:43:48,200
♪Reclaim the barren parts of life♪

938
00:43:48,200 --> 00:43:54,570
♪Walking this road
together, still hoping♪

939
00:43:55,360 --> 00:44:00,420
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

940
00:44:00,720 --> 00:44:04,690
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

941
00:44:04,920 --> 00:44:09,900
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

942
00:44:10,320 --> 00:44:14,880
♪Where fairness stands♪

943
00:44:15,350 --> 00:44:17,590
♪Within every heart♪

944
00:44:17,590 --> 00:44:20,240
♪So many voices calling♪

945
00:44:20,500 --> 00:44:24,790
♪Struggling, lost,
waiting for an answer♪

946
00:44:24,790 --> 00:44:27,140
♪Light up the lamps♪

947
00:44:27,140 --> 00:44:29,810
♪To answer those voices♪

948
00:44:30,120 --> 00:44:32,240
♪You deserve to be happy♪

949
00:44:32,240 --> 00:44:34,990
♪Loud and clear♪

950
00:44:34,990 --> 00:44:37,310
♪All the little things♪

951
00:44:37,310 --> 00:44:40,010
♪Woven into our lives♪

952
00:44:40,830 --> 00:44:42,880
♪The building blocks of life♪

953
00:44:42,880 --> 00:44:44,590
♪Shape the sky above us♪

954
00:44:44,590 --> 00:44:47,040
♪Are you doing alright?♪

955
00:44:47,040 --> 00:44:49,150
♪What are you struggling for?♪

956
00:44:49,400 --> 00:44:51,530
♪Some questions♪

957
00:44:52,100 --> 00:44:54,800
♪Weigh like mountains♪

958
00:44:57,690 --> 00:45:02,840
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

959
00:45:03,120 --> 00:45:07,130
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

960
00:45:07,310 --> 00:45:12,360
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

961
00:45:12,730 --> 00:45:16,430
♪Where fairness stands♪

962
00:45:16,600 --> 00:45:19,680
♪Within the law♪

963
00:45:20,840 --> 00:45:29,520
♪And within every heart♪
